title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a Wayang plan that checks the total purchases in 2025 from creditors with "VVS" in their name. It must also be creditors that do not have "SLETTET" in their name. Output in descending. I want creditor_id, creditor name and total price of each in my output. Output in textfile.

operations.table: (SELECT creditor_id, invoice_date, invoice_line_price FROM factpurchases) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val cid = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val price = r.getField(2).asInstanceOf[Double]; (cid, price) }

operations.table: (SELECT creditor_id, name FROM creditor) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val cid = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = r.getField(1).toString; (cid, name) }
(t: ((Int, Double), (Int, String))) => { val cid = t._1._1; val price = t._1._2; val name = t._2._2; (cid, name, price) }
(a: (Int, String, Double), b: (Int, String, Double)) => (a._1, a._2, a._3 + b._3)

log.thoughts: I built a plan that loads purchases for 2025, filters by creditor name containing VVS and excluding SLETTET, joins with creditor data to get names, aggregates total price per creditor, and outputs the results in descending order to a text file. The final output includes creditor_id, creditor name, and total price per creditor as requested.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT creditor_id, invoice_date, invoice_line_price FROM (SELECT creditor_id, invoice_date, invoice_line_price FROM factpurchases) as X) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val cid = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val price = r.getField(2).asInstanceOf[Double]; (cid, price) }

data.table: (SELECT creditor_id, name FROM (SELECT creditor_id, name FROM creditor) as X) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val cid = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = r.getField(1).toString; (cid, name) }
(t: ((Int, Double), (Int, String))) => { val cid = t._1._1; val price = t._1._2; val name = t._2._2; (cid, name, price) }
(a: (Int, String, Double), b: (Int, String, Double)) => (a._1, a._2, a._3 + b._3)
